AB  - Corrosion poses significant challenges across various industries, leading to economic losses and safety concerns. This comprehensive review explores recent advancements in corrosion prevention strategies, encompassing both traditional methods and emerging technologies. It begins with an overview of corrosion fundamentals and traditional techniques such as coatings, inhibitors, and cathodic protection, highlighting their strengths and limitations. Recent advancements, including innovative coatings, nanotechnology-based approaches, and smart materials with self-healing properties, are examined. The review also discusses computational modeling for accurate corrosion prediction, eco-friendly methods, and sustainable materials. Industry-specific applications are showcased for sectors such as oil and gas, automotive, aerospace, and marine. The review concludes with an analysis of current challenges, future directions, and opportunities for further research, providing valuable insights into the evolving landscape of corrosion prevention techniques.
